Combine cereal, dry milk, onion, ketchup, egg, salt and pepper. Add beef, mixing only until combined. Using level measuring-tablespoon, portion meat mixture. roll into balls and place in foil-lined shallow baking pan. Bake in 400 degrees F oven about 12 minutes or until browned. Drain off excess fat. In 4-quart saucepan, combine sauce ingredients. Simmer over low heat 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Add meatballs to sauce and continue simmering uncovered 10 minutes longer.